content.detailedDescription:
3 orbs in a triangular formation quickly and silently flew over our heads.

it was around 10:30pm on october 9th, 2015 and we were standing on the second floor, outside on the 1st floor roof at the back of our building in downtown hamilton near king east and ferguson.

we were talking about politics and all of a sudden in the corner my eye i saw 3 round and bright amber coloured orbs in a tight triangular formation go right over us.

the triangle was a very wide isosceles. it was so wide that it was almost as if the three orbs were together in a perfect line. except the middle orb was slightly ahead of the other two.

the directional flight path was coming from the north east, going south west.

they looked very low but hard to tell actual altitude, and i'd say around 2500feet above sea level.

speed looked to be anywhere around mach 1. reminded me completely of the fastest flybys one would see by a fast jet fighter at an airshow.
content.summary: Just saw three orbs in triangular formation fly over us extremely fast. right over hamilton from north east to south west. no sound what so ever.

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were going home (bridgton) on rt 302 heading north. we were driving past 'prism works' when my husband noticed them and told me to look up in the sky. it was still very light out, blue skies and barely a strand of clouds in the sky. the two crafts were far away and we were unable to tell the shape of them (possibly spherical), but they were the size of a bb (from a bb-gun)held at arms length. the two objects did not move, and did not disappear behind clouds (which tells me they were below cloud level). they looked as if they were blinking, because the sun was reflecting off of the metal surface.One of the crafts sat higher than the other, and they were close (3 inches apart from my point of view). due to our moving vehicle we lost sight of them behind the trees.
content.summary: Two stationary metal crafts in broad daylight

content.detailedDescription:
It's taken me 41 years to say anything about this to anyone other than family or my best friend that was with me when we say it.
we were on our way home from her boyfriends house about 10:30 at night, we were going north on catherdral oaks rd in goleta ca.  we noticed a light coming from the foothills to our right. this was really strange because there isn't anything out there except ranches, orchards and we later found out an electrical plant. i was about 17 and had grown up in goleta and i never knew there was an electrical plant back there. we first noticed it when we were about one mile from glen annie rd where we were going to make a left hand turn to go home. because there is nothing but ranches and orchards out there and no street lights it is dark, but i remember it was a clear night with lots of stars, so the light we saw really stood out. it was coming towards us but traveling above glenn annie rd from the hills. i was the first one to see it and pointed out to my bestfriend, neither of us knew what it was and i don't think neither of us really wanted to say what we thought it was, a ufo.  when we got to glenn annie to make our left turn this thing got there at the same time we did.  my bestfriend wanted to stop and check it out and i made her go. it hovered right above the eucalyptus trees and followed us for a couple of seconds. it was so low it felt like we could have touched it. then it was just gone, it went straight up and within seconds it was gone. on the rest of our ride home we were trying to figure out what we had seen. we went through a list, helicopter, plane, you name it we were thinking about it, everything but a ufo.  we decided that it had to be a ufo and we decided never to tell anyone about it. by this time we were both pretty shock up.  it scared me so bad that when i got home i went into my mom's room woke her up and slept with her for the next week.  i really thought they were going to come & get me. when my bestfriend got home she called me and we talked about it more. my mom checked with some people she knew that were in the air force and stationed at vandenberg afb and they hadn't heard of anything. they also told my mom that they see them a lot out on base. 

i forgot to describe it.  it was disc shaped and it had a white color light on the bottom until it started to leave then it turned a warm red color. it seemed like it was going to follow us.  it stayed right with us until we got to where we could see the lights from the gas station.

before this happened i really never gave ufos any thought but now i think about them a lot and when it's clear outside and we can see the stars i'm not only looking at the stars but looking to see if i see anything else flying around up there.  i really truly believe that people will not believe they are real until they actually see one and then some of them are going to try and explain them away, it's not that easy.
content.summary: Had a sighting of a craft that lasted several minutes.

now entrigued, i continued looking at the sky, and out of nowhere a cigar like craft appeared, shifted into an orb of light, then a fuzzy haze was around the ball of light and it dissappeared!
all while moving at a high rate of speed in a different direction than the disc a few minutes prior.
after another 10 minutes of staring at the sky, i noticed a very faint disc moving across the sky and dissappeared for 10 seconds... something is happening to ight?!?
please note that i do realize there are/were birds and planes in the sky also. these object were not any of them.

(some photos may have been lost with a refresh of my computer done by the manufacturer, when it locked up which was unrelated to the orb). 
i have attached photos of the orb from 9/8/15 to last night 10/9/15. i've included a shot of the orb with my pine tree for placement, and another of the moon last night and orb with city lights below for placement only, due to poor quality shots.

content.detailedDescription: I noticed a bright light in the sky out of my bedroom window. 6:35 am. it's still dark outside and i can see stars but this one thing about 60 degrees up in the sky was super bright.I was outside now. i have a star app and brought it up and it showed nothing where this large star like thing was. i have an iphone so i thought i'd take a video. in the video it just looks like a star not moving and that's why it's not included but if u want it i got it. anyway while i'm filming this thing i look up through a big hole in our trees and i see what looks kinda like a red star shoot out two objects with orange and blue lights. i couldn't tell if they were orbs or solid craft. i tried to video them but the film is just dark. they traveled away from the red star like a plane would but one was right behind the other. now if this isn't weird enough, i do an ancient practice called sun gazing. i go to a properly next door and down by the lake to watch the sun. it's 7:47 and i'm waiting for the sun to come up. i start seeing these lil flashes of light in the sky. kinda like when you're seeing spots or about to pass out but i was outside wide awake and felt fine. so i started to think.... are these far away? am i creating them? then i just focused my eyes and suddenly there were 50-100 fly sized luminous orbs floating around my body. some stayed floating around me for 10 min or so but others were like blinking in and out of reality. i had no idea what to think of this. they just looked like little intelligent balls of light. i tried to grab one but my hand went right threw it and it kept floating there. then after 10 min or so they just all disappeared. i don't know if all these events are related but it was one of the strangest mornings of my life. also 6 months ago i saw an orange ball of light 150 feet away from me across the road at the tops of the trees. this thing was super bright about the size of a basketball and u could see it had structure and energy or something swirling inside of it. about a block from where today's events happened.

content.detailedDescription:
At 7:25 am on friday, october 9, 2015, while heading north on hwy 215 i began to notice some bright lights in the sky near the airport. this is not uncommon, but the lights themselves were! i compared them to what were obviously planes coming and leaving from slc airport, and noticed several differences, which lead me to conclude that these might be ufos.

the lights in question were absolutely stationary. there was not a strong wind at the time, but planes do inch along in the sky, and there were conventional aircraft doing just that. the navigational lights of the planes were strong and steady, while the unknown lights i was witnessing scintillated like stars. the radiation of their lights was inconsistent; they pulsated rhythmically, and seemed to alternately glow very bright and get larger, and then diminish in luminosity and size to the point of disappearing. then they may – or may not – reappear! 

these ufos just hung there in the sky above the airport absolutely still while passenger planes came and went. i didn’t think to count them at the time, but i now estimate there were between 5-8 such lights positioned at various points in the sky. some were as far east as to be visible in front of the mountain range just north of the city, while others were much further west. the westernmost light was observed to get very low to the horizon in a slow, vertical descent, which made me wonder if it was landing! there was the main grouping of lights, which formed a line of three in a diagonal. 

for the most part, they just seemed to hang there in the sky, with the exception of the one that moved down slowly toward the horizon. i had to park my car at work and go in to start my day, but i did snap four pictures with my old school “dumb phone”, but even with computer enhancement later i can detect no trace of the ufos. in one photograph, i believe the descending ufo may be visible, but i cannot be certain. my photos reveal nothing, but even if they had, they would just be pinpoints of light in the sky above an airport; so what? the lights my eyes saw, however, were twinkling like stars, pulsating and changing in brightness. they were absolutely stationary.

i feel fairly certain that i was witness to an early morning display of extraterrestrial craft over salt lake city. then again, they could have been something sent up by hill air force base, but they certainly caught my attention because of their odd qualities and behavior.
content.summary: I saw lights in the sky above the slc airport that were not conventional terrestrial aircraft.

content.detailedDescription:
I'm an insomniac, & went outside onto my back deck to star gaze. there was a large, bright light over the mountains to the east of my home. i thought it was a wildfire (i had reported one in august in that area), until i realized it was a large bright white light over the mountain rather than on it. 
i then studied the light with my naked eye to rule out usual objects that i see in the night sky on a regular basis. i knew it to be none of the usual things, like: air planes, stars, meteor showers, ball lightning, etc. 
it hovered over the same location above a low mountain approx. 13 miles from my home (very near the location of the wildfires.) it appeared to have seven long spikes around the perimeter of the object. and the whole of the object was lit in a brilliant white light that pulsated, but not blinked.
i decided to get my game binoculars and my cell phone to study it further and take a photo (unfortunately my cell phone camera takes a poor picture.) using the binoculars i found that the object was stationary (and remained so for at least 45 minutes), but for one of the spikes that changed position to point down to the mountain/forest below. i also noted that the coloration of the object which i had thought to be white was lit on the right edge in a red/orange, and on the left edge in a blue/white. the whole of the object appeared prismatic not unlike a crystal. 
it stayed in that position for approximately 10 minutes after which the spikes shifted position to the left of the object in a ray-like fashion. it then departed eastward in a straight path until i could no longer see it. the departure happened in a matter of seconds.
content.summary: Star-like with 7 spokes/spikes
